Metadata: Novel marine sponge alkaloids 3. Beta-​carbolinium salts from "Fascaplysinops​is reticulata"

Very few alkaloids isolated from sponges have a beta-carboline skeleton. However, the pursuit of bioactive substances from the massive Indo-Pacific sponge "Fascaplysinops​is reticulata" has yielded unusual salts. Each has a sesterterpenoid anion associated with an alkaloid cation, and a new substituted beta- carboline arrangement is present in two of the three salts.
